­The Family of Professor Horace David Ritchie
Dedicate this bench to The Royal Parks
which they treasure.
Gordon, Andrew, Bruce, Blaise,
Maximillian, Ben, Imogen and Maya"²
¯DAVID BUCKNELL (DJB) 1939 - 2004
Bon viveur, raconteur, tin collector extraordinaire
was born to retire and went to Paradise by way of
Kensal Green (and a hostelry or two!)"·
´Peace be with you. Love to all.
Hope for our children.
Cherished son, brother, uncle, friend.
Adventurer and actor.
At one with nature, his spirit flies free.
Wise John Glynn."¹
